{"questionId":"20913","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Particle A travels in a straight line such that its displacement, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi></math> metres, from a fixed origin&nbsp;after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>10</mn></math>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/02915798495d49d6a9e8f1a26608c8f79648d79a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Particle A starts at the origin and passes through the origin again when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Particle A changes direction when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the distance of particle A from the origin when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mfenced><mn>10</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>distance</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mtext>s</mtext><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;integrating&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>distance</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20913","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.9c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the distance of particle A from the origin when t=10.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}